he could audition today.

1289
01:41:59.480 --> 01:42:01.679
He'd really be
perfect for this part.

1290
01:42:01.680 --> 01:42:03.799
Oh. this will break his heart.

1291
01:42:03.800 --> 01:42:06.439
Well is there any place
we can contact him?

1292
01:42:06.440 --> 01:42:08.879
Well. his beeper's
here on the table.

1293
01:42:08.880 --> 01:42:10.359
He took the kids to the zoo.

1294
01:42:10.360 --> 01:42:12.639
The zoo?
That's very. very sweet.

1295
01:42:12.640 --> 01:42:14.800
Which zoo? Oh. it's the
one with the white tiger.

1296
01:42:19.040 --> 01:42:21.360
Lionel Fisher.
I love your work.

1297
01:42:24.080 --> 01:42:26.000
Okay. please.
Look. I. uh..

1298
01:42:26.360 --> 01:42:27.800
I got my kids.

1299
01:42:28.880 --> 01:42:30.359
Get rid of them.

1300
01:42:30.360 --> 01:42:32.119
All right. guys. uh. guys.

1301
01:42:32.120 --> 01:42:35.000
Snack time. More
snacks. Here. go. go. go.

1302
01:42:36.640 --> 01:42:38.000
That's all. Uh..

1303
01:42:38.800 --> 01:42:41.240
It was just a job.
Nothing personal.

1304
01:42:41.680 --> 01:42:43.519
You know. I mean.
I play my part.

1305
01:42:43.520 --> 01:42:45.759
improvise a little. I mean.
it's what I'm good at..

1306
01:42:45.760 --> 01:42:48.440
I need to talk
to who's in charge.

1307
01:42:48.760 --> 01:42:50.040
Nobody knows.

1308
01:42:50.440 --> 01:42:52.319
I mean nobody
gets a big picture..

1309
01:42:52.320 --> 01:42:55.079
Hey. Tammy. Alex cut it out.
Damn it. why do they do that?

1310
01:42:55.080 --> 01:42:58.760
Your offices are empty. I need
to find out where they are.

1311
01:43:01.840 --> 01:43:02.960
Look.

1312
01:43:03.120 --> 01:43:05.399
they own the whole building.

1313
01:43:05.400 --> 01:43:07.319
They just move
from floor to floor.

1314
01:43:07.320 --> 01:43:08.680
And you work for them. right?

1315
01:43:08.920 --> 01:43:10.440
You can get me in.

1316
01:43:11.120 --> 01:43:13.040
No. I can't.
Oh. yes. you can.

1317
01:43:13.080 --> 01:43:16.319
You can tell them the police
called. You got to speak to someone.

1318
01:43:16.320 --> 01:43:18.239
You tell them I'm gonna
blow the whistle on them.

1319
01:43:18.240 --> 01:43:20.399
What whistle?
There's no fucking whistle.

1320
01:43:20.400 --> 01:43:22.640
This is very dangerous.

1321
01:43:24.880 --> 01:43:26.760
I don't think
that you understand.

1322
01:43:29.160 --> 01:43:30.360
Right now

1323
01:43:31.280 --> 01:43:32.399
I am

1324
01:43:32.400 --> 01:43:33.600
extremely

1325
01:43:33.800 --> 01:43:35.040
dangerous.

1326
01:43:38.120 --> 01:43:41.160
Michael. guys.
Come on. we're leaving.

1327
01:43:52.200 --> 01:43:53.360
Well we're here.

1328
01:43:53.760 --> 01:43:55.000
Drive in.

1329
01:44:00.240 --> 01:44:02.320
What're you gonna do. anyway?

1330
01:44:02.560 --> 01:44:04.239
You won't get your money back.

1331
01:44:04.240 --> 01:44:07.840
I don't care about money.
I'm pulling back the curtain.

1332
01:44:08.520 --> 01:44:10.000
I wanna meet the wizard.

1333
01:44:15.960 --> 01:44:18.000
He's eyeing us
like Tiffany Towers.

1334
01:44:18.200 --> 01:44:20.680
Pull in somewhere
where they won't see you.

1335
01:44:41.280 --> 01:44:43.040
Shit. Stay down. Stay down.

1336
01:44:48.800 --> 01:44:50.519
You're not allowed to be here.

1337
01:44:50.520 --> 01:44:51.560
They called me back.

1338
01:44:51.800 --> 01:44:53.000
I got a fitting.

1339
01:44:53.880 --> 01:44:55.280
He's with me.

1340
01:44:58.400 --> 01:45:00.560
You don't need me.
Shut up.

1341
01:45:01.400 --> 01:45:03.280
Get in.
Oh. my God.

1342
01:45:03.880 --> 01:45:05.560
Cuff him to the rail.

1343
01:45:10.880 --> 01:45:12.200
What floor?

1344
01:45:30.400 --> 01:45:34.040
You're fucked. you both.
They're gonna miss me.

1345
01:45:34.640 --> 01:45:36.959
Where? I told you they
hired me over the phone..

1346
01:45:36.960 --> 01:45:38.159
Where did you
pick up your checks?

1347
01:45:38.160 --> 01:45:39.559
It was a different floor then.

1348
01:45:39.560 --> 01:45:42.439
Then guess. I.. It went
on this way. sort of..

1349
01:45:42.440 --> 01:45:43.840
I don't know.

1350
01:45:47.040 --> 01:45:48.800
All right. take it easy.

1351
01:46:16.560 --> 01:46:18.480
It's gonna be a surprise.

1352
01:46:36.760 --> 01:46:38.600
Oh. fuck!

1353
01:46:40.520 --> 01:46:42.400
What are you doing here?

1354
01:46:43.200 --> 01:46:45.000
Back from the dead.

1355
01:46:54.400 --> 01:46:56.960
Nicholas. you're not
about to shoot anyone.

1356
01:46:57.520 --> 01:46:58.800
Turn around.

1357
01:47:06.680 --> 01:47:08.760
You're gonna come with me.

1358
01:47:09.040 --> 01:47:10.480
Everybody down!

1359
01:47:41.680 --> 01:47:43.040
Stop!

1360
01:47:51.160 --> 01:47:53.639
All right. what do you
think you're doing?

1361
01:47:53.640 --> 01:47:54.960
You tell me!

1362
01:47:55.800 --> 01:47:57.439
Who's behind this?

1363
01:47:57.440 --> 01:47:59.359
Who did this to me?
Why?

1364
01:47:59.360 --> 01:48:02.639
What do you mean. "Why?" How deluded
can you be? Who is responsible for this?

1365
01:48:02.640 --> 01:48:04.719
It wasn't you.
It wasn't personal.

1366
01:48:04.720 --> 01:48:07.360
It could've been any asshole with a
couple of hundred million in the bank.

1367
01:48:07.520 --> 01:48:09.679
Get on that radio. all right?
You get your boss up here.

1368
01:48:09.680 --> 01:48:11.679
You tell them
I'm gonna shoot somebody.

1369
01:48:11.680 --> 01:48:13.279
Who am I gonna call.
Nicholas? They won't do it.

1370
01:48:13.280 --> 01:48:15.559
Oh. yes. they will.
You get somebody up here

1371
01:48:15.560 --> 01:48:17.719
because I'm gonna kill you. They
don't care about me. Nicholas.

1372
01:48:17.720 --> 01:48:20.840
They'll let me die. You're not
in a position to threaten anyone.

1373
01:48:21.040 --> 01:48:22.399
Wait a minute.
Where'd you get that?

1374
01:48:22.400 --> 01:48:23.400
What?

1375
01:48:23.960 --> 01:48:26.599
That gun.
That's not an automatic.

1376
01:48:26.600 --> 01:48:28.199
What the fuck
are you talking about?

1377
01:48:28.200 --> 01:48:30.199
The guard had an automatic.
Where did you get the gun?

1378
01:48:30.200 --> 01:48:31.319
This is my gun.

1379
01:48:31.320 --> 01:48:32.760
But we searched the house.

1380
01:48:33.000 --> 01:48:34.879
Well I guess you missed this.
didn't you?

1381
01:48:34.880 --> 01:48:38.000
There's a situation up here. We
got a real goddamn gun up here..

1382
01:48:38.680 --> 01:48:40.839
Nicholas. it's fake.
It's a part of your game.

1383
01:48:40.840 --> 01:48:42.559
Don't you start with me now.
No. no. listen to me.

1384
01:48:42.560 --> 01:48:44.399
Don't you fucking start with me.
I'm telling you the truth now.

1385
01:48:44.400 --> 01:48:45.759
This is all the game.

1386
01:48:45.760 --> 01:48:47.759
Bullshit. all right? Bullshit.
I know what happened to that guy.

1387
01:48:47.760 --> 01:48:50.039
They shot that guy. Feingold. Fisher.
they killed him. What did you see?

1388
01:48:50.040 --> 01:48:51.559
Think about it. What'd you
see? I saw them kill him.

1389
01:48:51.560 --> 01:48:54.519
No. what'd you really
really see. this whole time?

1390
01:48:54.520 --> 01:48:57.399
Special effects. squibs.
Squibs like in the movies.

1391
01:48:57.400 --> 01:48:59.120
Nicholas. Nicholas. listen.

1392
01:49:00.560 --> 01:49:02.319
I've got a real gun
with real goddamned bullets..

1393
01:49:02.320 --> 01:49:04.400
Okay. okay.
I'll put it down.

1394
01:49:05.840 --> 01:49:09.039
Feingold. Mr. Fisher. He's on the
other side of that door. He's an actor.

1395
01:49:09.040 --> 01:49:10.919
You're trying to kill me. No
one's trying to kill you. Nicholas.

1396
01:49:10.920 --> 01:49:13.599
Please put that gun down. You're about
to make the biggest mistake of your life.

1397
01:49:13.600 --> 01:49:17.199
Nicholas. there was always a safety net.
The taxi. there was a diver. My house.

1398
01:49:17.200 --> 01:49:18.999
they shot at us with blanks.

1399
01:49:19.000 --> 01:49:20.039
It's not true.

1400
01:49:20.040 --> 01:49:21.839
It is. It's what
you hired us for.

1401
01:49:21.840 --> 01:49:24.399
They're waiting on the other
side of that door with champagne.

1402
01:49:24.400 --> 01:49:25.800
Nicholas.

1403
01:49:26.680 --> 01:49:29.879
Please. goddamn it!
Conrad. Conrad's there.

1404
01:49:29.880 --> 01:49:31.599
It's your birthday party.

1405
01:49:31.600 --> 01:49:33.080
You stop lying!

1406
01:49:35.800 --> 01:49:37.360
Let me show you.

1407
01:49:38.640 --> 01:49:40.440
Don't you move.

1408
01:49:41.320 --> 01:49:43.760
He's got a gun.
Get back from the door.

1409
01:49:57.480 --> 01:49:58.880
You shot him.

1410
01:50:06.000 --> 01:50:08.400
Someone..
Someone call an ambulance!

1411
01:50:28.280 --> 01:50:29.560
He's dead.

1412
01:50:34.600 --> 01:50:36.280
We thought you knew.

1413
01:50:40.240 --> 01:50:42.800
How did you let this
get so out of hand?

1414
01:50:43.920 --> 01:50:45.920
He wouldn't listen to me.

1415
01:50:49.040 --> 01:50:51.280
We went through this
over and over.

1416
01:50:55.560 --> 01:50:58.000
The mark is
your responsibility.

1417
01:50:58.640 --> 01:50:59.720
You never.

1418
01:51:00.240 --> 01:51:02.640
never let the mark take over.

1419
01:51:04.880 --> 01:51:07.400
I'm sorry. He could
have almost killed us.

1420
01:51:08.960 --> 01:51:10.840
I had a walkie-talkie.

1421
01:51:11.160 --> 01:51:13.080
I used the walkie-talkie.

1422
01:51:15.640 --> 01:51:17.119
We're going to jail.

1423
01:51:17.120 --> 01:51:20.560
We're all going to jail
for the rest of our lives.

1424
01:51:30.400 --> 01:51:31.680
Oh. God.

1425
01:51:33.080 --> 01:51:34.320
Nicholas!

1426
01:52:08.120 --> 01:52:09.959
We've got him.
He's in the bag.

1427
01:52:09.960 --> 01:52:12.400
We have him here.
He came in right on target.

1428
01:52:15.080 --> 01:52:18.360
Keep everyone back until we
clear away the breakaway glass.

1429
01:52:19.960 --> 01:52:21.799
Mr. Van Orton.
don't open your eyes.

1430
01:52:21.800 --> 01:52:24.680
It's just breakaway glass.
but it can still cut you.

1431
01:52:26.120 --> 01:52:27.799
Just gonna take a look at you.

1432
01:52:27.800 --> 01:52:29.600
I'm gonna check your pulse.

1433
01:52:34.360 --> 01:52:37.040
Just take it easy.
That was quite a fall.

1434
01:53:07.400 --> 01:53:09.200
Happy birthday. Nickie.

1435
01:53:21.120 --> 01:53:22.800
What is this?

1436
01:53:23.520 --> 01:53:25.440
It's your birthday present.

1437
01:53:44.600 --> 01:53:47.640
I had to do something. You
were becoming such an asshole.

1438
01:53:58.800 --> 01:54:01.480
Ladies and gentlemen. My
brother. Nicholas Van Orton.

1439
01:54:35.360 --> 01:54:39.279
Amazing. I just wanted
to tell you. Great job.

1440
01:54:39.280 --> 01:54:41.200
This was the best ever.

1441
01:54:42.840 --> 01:54:44.879
Thank God you jumped.
Because if you didn't.

1442
01:54:44.880 --> 01:54:46.559
I was supposed
to throw you off.

1443
01:54:46.560 --> 01:54:47.840
Thanks.

1444
01:54:48.880 --> 01:54:51.960
We have to head home. We
just wanted to say goodbye.

1445
01:54:52.360 --> 01:54:53.680
Rachel.

1446
01:54:54.040 --> 01:54:55.440
Sweet dreams.

1447
01:54:57.560 --> 01:55:01.439
Thanks. Mel. for coming. I'm
sorry about your car. I..

1448
01:55:01.440 --> 01:55:03.680
I think I left it at the zoo.
No problem.

1449
01:55:10.080 --> 01:55:11.960
Happy birthday. Nicholas.

1450
01:55:14.120 --> 01:55:16.160
I'll call you.
I really will.

1451
01:55:31.480 --> 01:55:34.840
Nicholas. I haven't a clue
what this is all about.

1452
01:55:35.000 --> 01:55:38.159
Your taste in champagne
is excellent as always.

1453
01:55:38.160 --> 01:55:39.920
It was a great entrance.

1454
01:55:41.240 --> 01:55:43.199
Yes. and I want you to know that
what happened on Sunday was..

1455
01:55:43.200 --> 01:55:44.720
Oh. no. no. please.

1456
01:55:45.080 --> 01:55:47.639
I've never been happier
in my whole life.

1457
01:55:47.640 --> 01:55:49.359
I thank you.

1458
01:55:49.360 --> 01:55:51.280
And my wife thanks you.

1459
01:55:52.920 --> 01:55:54.640
Thank you for coming.

1460
01:55:55.200 --> 01:55:56.720
Thank you. Sam.

1461
01:55:59.400 --> 01:56:00.559
What's this?

1462
01:56:00.560 --> 01:56:02.240
This is

1463
01:56:04.080 --> 01:56:05.320
the bill.

1464
01:56:06.600 --> 01:56:07.999
The bill?

1465
01:56:08.000 --> 01:56:09.400
Keep the pen.

1466
01:56:10.720 --> 01:56:12.360
Thank you. both.

1467
01:56:19.520 --> 01:56:20.720
You wanna split it?

1468
01:56:20.760 --> 01:56:23.600
Oh. God. yes. please.
I'll take you up on that.

1469
01:56:25.400 --> 01:56:26.720
Oh. my God.

1470
01:56:31.040 --> 01:56:32.680
Thank you. Connie.

1471
01:56:36.320 --> 01:56:38.599
What happened to that

1472
01:56:38.600 --> 01:56:40.720
waitress?
What was her name. uh..

1473
01:56:41.200 --> 01:56:42.240
Christine?

1474
01:56:42.480 --> 01:56:44.279
She said something
about catching a plane.

1475
01:56:44.280 --> 01:56:46.960
I just saw her out front
trying to hail a cab.

1476
01:57:05.200 --> 01:57:06.520
Christine?

1477
01:57:08.920 --> 01:57:10.240
I. um..

1478
01:57:10.480 --> 01:57:12.399
I didn't get a chance
to say goodbye.

1479
01:57:12.400 --> 01:57:14.040
Thank you. I..

1480
01:57:14.200 --> 01:57:17.079
You know. I never did
ask you your name. did I?

1481
01:57:17.080 --> 01:57:18.240
No.

1482
01:57:18.480 --> 01:57:19.999
It's

1483
01:57:20.000 --> 01:57:21.199
Claire.

1484
01:57:21.200 --> 01:57:24.119
So you catching a plane or..

1485
01:57:24.120 --> 01:57:26.999
Yeah. we have a gig starting
next week in Australia. so..

1486
01:57:27.000 --> 01:57:28.799
Gonna shear some more sheep.

1487
01:57:28.800 --> 01:57:30.359
Just a walk-on this time.

1488
01:57:30.360 --> 01:57:32.400
Well. when you get back.

1489
01:57:35.120 --> 01:57:37.680
maybe. you know.
we could have some dinner.

1490
01:57:38.640 --> 01:57:40.920
You don't know
anything about me.

1491
01:57:41.320 --> 01:57:42.800
No. I don't.

1492
01:57:43.320 --> 01:57:44.560
So you tell me.

1493
01:57:44.800 --> 01:57:46.280
Well. what..
Where you're from?

1494
01:57:48.360 --> 01:57:49.600
Originally.

1495
01:57:49.960 --> 01:57:51.240
Oklahoma.

1496
01:57:52.160 --> 01:57:53.360
Colorado?

1497
01:57:56.760 --> 01:57:58.960
I've been doing this
for way too long.

1498
01:58:01.160 --> 01:58:02.600
You know.

1499
01:58:04.680 --> 01:58:06.080
would you like to

1500
01:58:06.480 --> 01:58:08.640
have coffee with me
at the airport?

1501
01:58:22.000 --> 01:58:25.000
<font face="Vrinda">{\an5}
<b>SubText: NoRMITA.326</b></font>
